01:16:30.919 --> 01:16:33.919
It's a table, it's still a table stakes to be like a usable LSP.

01:16:33.919 --> 01:16:34.919
We have to have like good auto complete.

01:16:34.919 --> 01:16:40.919
But it is like, you know, the way that like agents would use that tool is going to be like really different.

01:16:40.919 --> 01:16:44.919
And so, you know, at least I'm thinking about it a lot.

01:16:44.919 --> 01:16:50.919
Like, you know, I think I've always tried to think ever since like AI became really usable.

01:16:50.919 --> 01:16:53.919
I've just thought a lot about how can we make sure what we're building is resilient.

01:16:53.919 --> 01:16:56.919
Because like we really cannot predict the future.

01:16:56.919 --> 01:17:01.919
But like we can think about like what's going to be resilient and what's not.

01:17:01.919 --> 01:17:06.919
So like static analysis, like having really good verification, like really fast verification.

01:17:06.919 --> 01:17:09.919
Like that's, in my opinion, like very resilient.

01:17:09.919 --> 01:17:14.919
Like as you write Python, I think like typing, for example, will only become like more important and more useful.

01:17:14.919 --> 01:17:16.919
Because it's a very fast way to validate correctness.

01:17:16.919 --> 01:17:18.919
And then package management.

01:17:18.919 --> 01:17:22.919
It's like, okay, like I mean maybe there's a world where you have no dependencies.

01:17:22.919 --> 01:17:24.919
And you're like building all of everything from scratch.

01:17:24.919 --> 01:17:26.919
But like I think we're like much further away from that.

01:17:26.919 --> 01:17:29.919
And so, you know, being able to install and manage your dependency tool chain.

01:17:29.919 --> 01:17:31.919
Making it really easy to start and run your project.

01:17:31.919 --> 01:17:35.919
Like those are things that to me, I feel like we're making very resilient bets.

01:17:35.919 --> 01:17:38.919
But we also have to be thinking a lot, you know, just about how it's changing.

